<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="41" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[136,1452,1310,2021]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">
The protologue of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Carriere 1866: 106)" baseAuthorityName="Carriere" baseAuthorityPageNumber="106" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[350,767,1310,1337]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="numidica">
<emphasis box="[350,525,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">Abies numidica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Carriere, E. A." box="[541,759,1310,1337]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" pagination="106 - 107" refId="ref7891" refString="Carriere, E. A. (1866) Abies numidina. Revue Horticole (Paris) 37: 106 - 107. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 196547  page / 132 / mode / 1 up]" type="journal article" year="1866">Carrière 1866: 106</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
includes a complete and extensive description of this plant, a diagnosis to differentiate it from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Antoine" authorityYear="1841" baseAuthorityName="Boiss." box="[538,660,1347,1373]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pinsapo">
<emphasis box="[538,660,1347,1373]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">A. pinsapo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and several comments about the locality: “confinée dans la Kabylie algérienne, cette ancienne province à laquelle les Romains avaient donné le nom de 
<emphasis box="[1154,1249,1382,1408]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">Numidie</emphasis>
. Elle habite tout particulièrement les monts Tababor et Grand-Babor, à une altitude assez élevée pour que, dans certains endroits, la neige soit presque permanente”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[136,1452,1310,2021]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">The protologue also includes relevant comments referring to the studied gatherings: “A plusieurs reprises, il a eu l’obligeance de m’envoyer des échantillons à divers états de cette espèce, et c’est d’après ceux-ci que j’ai fait la description ci-dessus”.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[136,1452,1310,2021]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">
<materialsCitation collectorName="M. Delannoy" location="Mt Tababor Kabylie province" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Constantine" typeStatus="syntype">
<bibRefCitation author="Farjon, A." box="[189,405,1598,1624]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" refId="ref8781" refString="Farjon, A. (2010) A handbook of the world's conifers, vol. 1. Brill Academic Publishers, Leiden &amp; Boston, 1111 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 9789047430629" type="book" year="2010">Farjon (2010: 108)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned “Type not designated”. We have located a specimen relevant at P, with barcode P00507232. This specimen bears a stem well preserved, with leaves, and a label annotated as “Herb. Mus. Paris. / 
<taxonomicName authority="Delannoy" authorityName="de Lannoy ex Carriere, P" authorityYear="1866" box="[136,428,1670,1696]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="numidica">Abies numidica Delannoy</taxonomicName>
/ 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03FF903F4B11FF9F14F9D58FFE5BF80B:8E8977F24B11FF9F15B3D7DEFCE9F94E" box="[450,777,1670,1697]" name="Mt Tababor Kabylie province" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" stateProvince="Constantine">
<superScript attach="left" box="[450,480,1670,1697]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">Mt</superScript>
Tababor Kabylie province
</location>
/ In 
<collectingRegion box="[829,963,1670,1696]" country="Algeria" name="Constantine" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">Constantine</collectingRegion>
/ Donné par 
<collectorName box="[1109,1260,1670,1697]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">M. Delannoy</collectorName>
” (
<figureCitation box="[1284,1352,1670,1697]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[136,229,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[274,1314,190,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-20@12.[274,1314,190,1929]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Lectotype of Abies numidica de Lannoy ex Carrière, P (barcode P00507232). Photography courtesy of Herbarium P; reproduced with permission." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605324" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605324/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Maybe this specimen could be treated as a “ 
<typeStatus box="[535,630,1706,1732]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">syntype</typeStatus>
”. However, it is clearly relevant that the specimen lacks any annotation by Carrière that undoubtedly links it to the material mentioned by Carrière in the prologue. The specimen does not have the collection date. In addition, there is also no evidence or any link to consider the specimen at P as part of the material sent by Lannoy to Carrière before the publication of the protologue. Therefore, unfortunately, this material cannot be indubitably considered as original material according to 
<emphasis box="[768,815,1851,1877]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">ICN</emphasis>
Art. 9.4
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[136,1452,1310,2021]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">
<materialsCitation collectorName="Lannoy" county="Kabylie" location="Alizoti" municipality="Tababor" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Constantine" typeStatus="neotype">
However, the specimen P00507232 is the only material that we have found collected by 
<collectorName box="[1186,1272,1887,1913]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">Lannoy</collectorName>
in the localities cited in the protologue (
<collectingRegion box="[413,551,1922,1948]" country="Algeria" name="Constantine" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">Constantine</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCounty box="[565,656,1922,1948]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">Kabylie</collectingCounty>
, 
<collectingMunicipality box="[670,767,1922,1949]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">Tababor</collectingMunicipality>
). The specimen is well preserved and clearly represents the traditional concept and current application of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Lannoy ex Carriere, P" authorityYear="1866" box="[644,778,1958,1985]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="numidica">
<emphasis box="[644,661,1959,1985]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[674,778,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">numidica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03FF903F4B11FF9F14F9D58FFE5BF80B:8E8977F24B11FF9F1769D6FFFC88F82E" box="[792,872,1958,1984]" county="Kabylie" municipality="Tababor" name="Alizoti" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" stateProvince="Constantine">Alizoti</location>
<emphasis box="[878,934,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">et al.</emphasis>
201, 
<bibRefCitation author="Farjon, A." box="[995,1135,1958,1984]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" refId="ref8820" refString="Farjon, A. (2017) A handbook of the world's conifers, 2 nd ed., vol. 1. Brill Academic Publishers, Leiden &amp; Boston, 1153 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 9789004324510" type="book" year="2017">Farjon 2017</bibRefCitation>
). This material is designated as the 
<typeStatus box="[208,297,1995,2021]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">neotype</typeStatus>
of the name
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
